			<text>
			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="14"></font><br><br><font size="13">Marine vessels, buoys and offshore structures spend a large part of their working life partly submerged in water. As a result they become easily colonised by the many micro-organisms that live in the water, especially when stationary.<br><br>The extent of this colonisation, also known as fouling, depends on salinity, water temperature and productivity of the organic matter on which the organisms feed.</font></textformat>]]>
			</text>
