			<text>
			<![CDATA[<textformat leading="12"><font size="14"></font><br><br><font size="13">The marine organism can either be of plant origin such as weeds and algae, or of animal origin such as tubeworms and barnacles.<br><br>To protect the boat from colonisation, anti-fouling treatments such as paint are applied to the outer parts of the ship at regular intervals. The coating is designed to gradually leach biocide or a toxin into the marine environment. This slow poisoning prevents organisms from sticking to the hull.</font></textformat>]]>
			</text>
